Two Uighurs sentenced to death in China for terrorism - News - World - The Voice of Russia: News, Breaking news, Politics, Economics, Business, Russia, International current events, Expert opinion, podcasts, Video
Two Uighurs were sentenced to death and three others given long jail terms for their role in a fatal confrontation with police in north-western China, state news agency Xinhua reported late Monday.
The Intermediate People's Court in Kashgar prefecture, in the restive region of Xinjiang, sentenced Musa Hesen to death for murder, and organizing and leading a terrorist group. Another man, Rehman Hupur, was sentenced to death for murder and participating in a terrorist group, Xinhua reported.
Three others were given prison terms of between nine years and life, the agency reported.
Twenty-one people died in clashes between police and ethnic Uighurs on April 23 in Bachu county near China's westernmost city of Kashgar, after police raided a suspected militant hideout.